# FFI Test Results
%%%
tag := "ffi-test-results"
%%%

{index}[FFI test results]
The FFI layer is tested through three independent paths:

## Python FFI Tests
%%%
tag := "python-ffi-results"
%%%

Two Python test suites validate the `ctypes`-based bindings:

 * _FFI Integration Tests_ (`Tests/test_python_ffi.py`) —
   tests the C shared library directly from Python
 * _Package Tests_ (`python/tests/`) —
   tests the `lean4yaml` Python package API

Results are captured as both text logs and JUnit XML,
with an HTML report generated from the JUnit data.

## Cross-Language Comparison
%%%
tag := "cross-lang-results"
%%%

{index}[cross-language comparison]
The cross-language comparison runs the full yaml-test-suite
through all four backends (Lean, C, Python, Rust) across
five limit presets (`unlimited`, `default`, `strict`,
`permissive`, `safe_tags`).

This verifies that the FFI layer preserves identical parsing
behavior — every backend must produce the same pass/fail/skip
results for every test case under every preset configuration.

# yaml-test-suite Coverage
%%%
tag := "suite-coverage-results"
%%%

{index}[yaml-test-suite coverage]
The `suiterunner` executable generates detailed HTML coverage
reports showing per-test-ID results across all YAML categories:

 * Block structure (sequences, mappings, scalars)
 * Flow collections
 * Document markers
 * Directives and tags
 * Error handling and edge cases

Coverage reports are available as interactive HTML pages in the
`test-results/` directory alongside this documentation.
